<P>
ROBERT COCHRAN CURRIER; FOUNDER OF PLAYHOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Robert Cochran Currier, 77, founder of the Kennebunkport (Maine) Playhouse 
which featured famed actors of the 1930s. 
</P>
<P>
He also was an actor who toured in plays with such actresses as Kathryn Cornell 
and Cornelia Otis Skinner. Currier had founded the Garrick Players, out of 
which grew the Kennebunkport repertory group. In Desert Hot Springs, Calif., on 
April 15. 
</P>
</TEXT>
