<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Olivia Maria De La Torre, 25, who escaped last week from the Las Colinas 
Women's Jail, was recaptured Monday in a Southeast San Diego alley. 
</P>
<P>
De La Torre, who was awaiting sentencing on a drug conviction and probation 
violation when she escaped Wednesday, was taken into custody by parole agents 
and San Diego police officers. 
</P>
<P>
Police spokesman Bill Robinson said she was carrying a rock cocaine pipe when 
she was arrested at 8:50 a.m. in an alley at the 2600 block of Imperial Avenue. 
</P>
