<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beckman Instruments Inc.: The Fullerton company reported first-quarter profit 
of $8 million, down 25% from the same period in 1989. 
</P>
<P>
Sales for the quarter were $185.5 million, a decrease of 7% from the year 
before. The decrease was blamed on a reduction in government funding for 
biological research, unusually large shipments in the 1989 quarter, a movement 
by customers toward operating leases instead of purchases and an increase in 
research and development expenses. Beckman develops and manufactures automated 
systems and supplies used in biological research laboratories. 
</P>
</TEXT>
