EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CalFed Inc.: The Los Angeles parent of California Federal Bank said 
first-quarter net income rose 8% to $18.9 million. 
</P>
<P>
Net interest income in the financial services segment, the primary source of 
earnings, grew 28% to $128.5 million. CalFed's results benefited from a 
$1.3-million net gain on the sale of its London-based Anglo American Insurance 
Co. unit. California Federal Bank's interest rate spread at March 31 was 2.24%, 
compared to 1.47% a year before. 
</P>
</TEXT>
