</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Castle &amp; Cooke Inc.: First-quarter profit increased 45% to $18.1 million 
compared to the same period in 1989, while revenue rose 17% to $658 million. 
</P>
<P>
The fresh fruit group's Chilean operations returned to profitability, while the 
fresh vegetable group suffered from lower lettuce prices. Profitability of the 
packaged foods operations was decreased by an expansion of the consumer product 
lines. Real estate operations improved due to increased residential sales in 
Hawaii and commercial property sales in California. The Los Angeles holding 
company operates Dole Food Co. and does real estate development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
