<TEXT>
<P>
ReadiCare Inc.: The Irvine developer and operator of workers' compensation 
medical centers and rehabilitation programs reported net income of $1.7 million 
for its fiscal year ended Feb. 28. 
</P>
<P>
A year earlier, the company lost $3.6 million, which included a non-recurring 
charge of $4.4 million from discontinued activities. Revenue rose 4%, to $20.2 
million from $19.4 million. For the fourth quarter, net income was $248,000, 
contrasted with a loss of $4.4 million for the like period a year earlier. 
Revenue increased 4.3%, to $4.9 million from $4.7 million. 
</P>
