<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: REXHALL POSTS RISE IN QUARTERLY PROFIT, SALES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rexhall Industries Inc., a Santa Clarita builder of motor homes, said its 
first-quarter profit rose 34% from a year earlier as sales jumped 85%. 
</P>
<P>
In the quarter ended March 31, Rexhall's earnings climbed to $477,000 from 
$356,000 and its sales surged to $10.9 million from $5.87 million. 
</P>
<P>
Rexhall, whose products are sold through 81 dealers, said it plans to increase 
production and add dealers in the United States, Europe and Japan. The company 
also recently opened a second plant in Santa Clarita to build a new line of 
motor homes. 
</P>
