<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Garbo a Paul Lynde Fan?: What did Greta Garbo do while she was alone all that 
time? She watched a lot of TV, according to People magazine. 
</P>
<P>
Although the reclusive star collected valuable art and antiques (her will named 
her niece as sole beneficiary), her taste in television was rather pedestrian. 
Raymond Daum, a friend of the actress, told the magazine that Garbo once said, 
"If a program is advertised as experimental, I never turn it on." Kenny 
Kingston, a psychic whom Garbo consulted, says she was especially enthralled by 
"Hollywood Squares": "She adored Paul Lynde. I think she even wrote him a fan 
letter." GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
