<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: WEEKEND BOX OFFICE; 
</P>
<P>
NINJA TURTLES RIDING A WAVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAT H. BROESKE SOURCES: Exhibitor Relations Co. , Arts and entertainment 
reports from The Times, national and international news services and the 
nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles" continues to dominate the box office. With 
weekend ticket sales of $9.7 million, New Line Cinema's PG-rated turtle tale 
has now grossed $89 million. 
</P>
<P>
Touchstone Pictures' R-rated romance, "Pretty Woman," also continues its 
winning streak. Weekend ticket sales of $8.3 million bring its grosses to $71.7 
million. Meanwhile, with receipts of $3.5 million -- and grosses of $95 million 
-- Paramount Pictures' "The Hunt for Red October" is now cruising toward the 
prestigious $100-million mark. 
</P>
<P>
Among new titles, only Orion Pictures' "Miami Blues" placed in the Top Five. 
The black and blue (and blood-red) comedy-drama, about the exploits of a 
sometimes-likable sociopath (Alec Baldwin), earned about $3 million. 
</P>
<P>
* MGM/UA's just-out "Lisa," about a terrorized teen-ager, grossed $1.1 million 
in limited release at 287 theaters, for a solid per-screen average of $3,902. 
</P>
