</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Mikhail S. Gorbachev has ordered the operation of special Aeroflot 
flights to Saudi Arabia to allow Soviet Muslims to make the ritual pilgrimage 
to Mecca, his spokesman, Arkady A. Maslennikov, said. Starting in June, the 
flights are to leave for Jidda, Saudi Arabia, from Moscow and several other 
Soviet cities with large Muslim populations. The two nations do not have 
diplomatic relations. 
