<P>
The Cypriot government approved continuation of its spring hunting season, the 
last in Europe, despite strong opposition from environmental groups. 
</P>
<P>
In announcing the season, which began Sunday, Interior Ministry game department 
chief Costas Papamichael rejected charges that the season amounts to a 
slaughter. He insisted that hunters "are very lucky if they get two birds and 
are normally quite satisfied with that." Environmental groups oppose the spring 
hunting because it falls during the breeding season of migratory birds. 
