<P>
'GLACIER' OF LAVA DESTROYS 3 HOMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A massive "glacier" of molten rock from erupting Kilauea Volcano destroyed 
three more homes in a rural housing area near Kalapana, Hawaii, civil defense 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The lava flow from the volcano has destroyed 10 homes in four days. The flow 
has halted no more than 40 feet away from another dwelling, following its 
pattern of spending long periods reinflating and then suddenly surging forward 
to engulf more land. "It's stopped, but it's still hot underneath. We don't 
know where it will break out yet," said a civil defense worker. 
</P>
