<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAYOR PLANS WASHINGTON PITCH FOR METRO RAIL 
FUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles Mayor Tom Bradley is traveling to Washington this week in a quest 
for more federal funds to help build the Metro Rail subway from MacArthur Park 
to Hollywood, the mayor's office announced Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Bradley is to be one of several Los Angeles officials testifying at the House 
Appropriations subcommittee on transportation hearing this afternoon. A Bradley 
spokesman said the local delegation is seeking $185 million during the next 
fiscal year for the 6.8-mile extension of the Metro Rail system. The federal 
government recently allocated $667 million for the segment. 
</P>
