JUNTA PUTS DOWN 2ND COUP ATTEMPT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For the second time in a month, Sudan's military government crushed a revolt by 
junior army officers. The country's military leader, Lt. Gen. Omar Hassan 
Bashir, said in a broadcast on government radio that loyalist forces arrested 
the rebels and maintained control of the East African nation. He did not give 
casualty figures or the number of arrests. 
</P>
