<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WOMEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
Twentieth-ranked US International improved to 16-9 with a 5-1 victory over 
Hawaii. 
</P>
<P>
Playing at No. 1 singles, USIU's Carol Curmi defeated Hawaii's Justine Tate, 
6-2, 6-2. USIU's Diane Lowings defeated Karen Felicihda of Hawaii (20-14), 4-6, 
6-4, 6-4, at No. 2 singles. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
UC-Irvine, ranked 19th, led San Diego State, 4-1, when the match was suspended 
because of rain. Eighteenth-ranked Trevor Kronenmann of UCI (17-11) defeated 
Ricardo Herrera, ranked 97th, 7-5, 6-3. Eighty-fourth-ranked Tole Marincovic of 
SDSU (18-7), defeated Richard Lubner, ranked 25th, 6-1, 6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
