<P>
ARSON ARREST MADE AFTER 2 HOUSE FIRES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man was arrested on suspicion of arson Monday after firefighters put out two 
small house fires that authorities believe were started by Molotov cocktails. 
</P>
<P>
David Lopez, 20, of Orange allegedly threw glass containers with flammable 
liquid at occupied houses in the 400 and 500 block of North Lemon Street about 
2 a.m. Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Police Sgt. Robert Gustafson said none of the occupants of the houses were 
injured. 
</P>
<P>
Damage was estimated at $5,000 to one of the houses, and at $150 to the other. 
</P>
<P>
Police arrested Lopez about two hours after the fires, using a description of 
the getaway vehicle provided by a witness, Gustafson said. Lopez was being held 
in Orange County Jail on suspicion of arson of inhabited structures, Gustafson 
said. His bail was set at $25,000. 
</P>
<P>
Gustafson said no motive has been established. The police investigation is 
continuing. 
</P>
