<P>
RUNOFF CANDIDATE SUES FOE FOR $6 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONG BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Council candidate Jim Serles has filed a $6-million libel suit against opponent 
Doug Drummond, claiming Drummond defamed him with claims that Serles struck 
"back room deals" and "sold his vote" while he was chairman of the city's 
Planning Commission. 
</P>
<P>
At issue is campaign literature circulated by Drummond before the April 10 
election, which Serles was heavily favored to win. Drummond forced Serles into 
a June runoff. 
</P>
<P>
The literature depicted a newspaper clipping saying that Serles was under 
investigation by the state Fair Political Practices Commission, when no such 
article existed, the suit said. The literature also included a photo of Serles 
emblazoned with the words "For Sale." 
