<HEADLINE>
<P>
UC IRVINE GUARD PLANS TRANSFER TO LSU 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ELLIOTT TEAFORD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Justin Anderson, a 6-foot-5 junior guard from UC Irvine, has asked for and been 
given his release from the school. 
</P>
<P>
Anderson, who averaged 8.1 points and started 13 games for the Anteaters last 
season, told Irvine Coach Bill Mulligan he plans to transfer to Louisiana 
State. 
</P>
<P>
Dale Brown, LSU coach, recruited Anderson when the guard was at Valley City 
High School in North Dakota. As a senior, Anderson averaged 22 points and 10 
rebounds and was named the state's player of the year. Brown and Anderson's 
father, Darrell, played one season together at Minot State. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm really happy for him," Mulligan said. "I was surprised. I thought he was 
more into academics than basketball." 
</P>
<P>
Anderson, an engineering and psychology major, will redshirt the 1990-91 season 
and have one year of eligibility remaining at LSU. 
</P>
<P>
Last season at Irvine, Anderson's playing time decreased as freshman Dylan 
Rigdon emerged as the Anteaters's top outside shooter. ELLIOTT TEAFORD 
</P>
</TEXT>
