<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. MARIACHI BAND JOINS FESTIVAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ZAN DUBIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mariachi Uclatlan, a mariachi band based in Orange, has been added to the 
growing list of groups and artists from Orange County to participate in 
September's Los Angeles Festival of the arts. 
</P>
<P>
The 12-member band, which regularly performs at El Mariachi restaurant in 
Orange, is scheduled to play at a gathering "of the best mariachi in the 
greater Los Angeles area," said Judy Mitoma, festival co-curator. 
</P>
<P>
Other recently confirmed festival participants from Orange County are San Juan 
Capistrano photographer Mihoko Yamagata, to be featured in a solo exhibit, and 
Florinda Mintz, a writer from Santa Ana who is co-organizing a mini-festival of 
poets from Latin America and Canada. Mintz said Pablo Antonio Cuadra, one of 
Nicaragua's leading poets and director of the newspaper La Prensa, will be 
among those reading their work. 
</P>
<P>
The mariachi gathering, the Yamagata exhibit and the poetry mini-festival all 
will be subsidized by the festival. An "open" segment of the festival will 
feature other artists, including several from Orange County, who will pay to 
present their work. All events will take place throughout Los Angeles County. 
ZAN DUBIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
