ROCKY HILL, Conn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ames Department Stores Inc. has hired a bankruptcy specialist from a prominent 
New York law firm, fueling speculation that the retailer will file for 
protection from its creditors under the federal bankruptcy code, according to a 
published report. 
</P>
<P>
A story in today's editions of the Hartford Courant said Ames has hired Michael 
Cook of Skadden, Arps, Slate, Meagher &amp; Flom to begin preparing paper work 
for a Chapter 11 filing, which would allow Ames to continue operating while 
trying to work out a plan to repay its debts. 
</P>
<P>
Ames, which has been suffering from major losses and cash flow shortages since 
its 1988 acquisition of the Zayre discount chain, has been trying for weeks to 
negotiate new financing with its bankers. Most of its stores are in the 
Northeast, where the retail environment is sluggish. 
