<TEXT>
<P>
Spanish film director Pedro Almodovar lost a bid today to lift an X rating the 
Motion Picture Assn. of America gave his latest film, "Tie Me Up! Tie Me Down." 
</P>
<P>
The MPAA's appeals board voted 6-6 to sustain the rating despite an impassioned 
plea by civil rights lawyer William Kunstler. A rating can be overturned only 
with a two-thirds majority vote. 
</P>
<P>
At issue was a sex scene in Almodovar's film, "Tie Me Up! Tie Me Down," a black 
comedy about an escaped mental patient who kidnaps a porn actress and then gets 
her to fall in love with him by tying her up. The X rating restricts audiences 
to age 17 and older. 
